'''Purificacion Valera Quisumbing''' (c. 1934 – December 1, 2011) was a [[Philippines|Filipino]] [[human rights activist]] who served as the Chairperson of [[Commission on Human Rights (Philippines)|Commission on Human Rights]] from 2002 to 2008.<ref name=mb>{{cite news|first=Florangel|last=Rosario Braid|title=Tribute to an H.R. defender|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/articles/344274/tribute-hr-defender|work=[[Manila Bulletin]]|publisher=|date=2011-12-09|accessdate=2011-12-28}}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
In March 2011, the [[United Nations Human Rights Council]] re-elected Quisumbing to a second, three-year term on the council's advisory committee.<ref name=hyrbid>{{cite news|first=Tonyo|last=Cruz |title=Filipino reelected to UN Human Rights Council advisory panel |url=http://asiancorrespondent.com/51385/filipino-reelected-to-un-human-rights-council-advisory-panel/ |work=[[Hybrid News]] |publisher= |date=2011-12-09 |accessdate=2011-03-29}}</ref>
Quisumbing died on December 1, 2011, at the age of 77.<ref name=mb/> She was survived by her husband, [[Leonardo Quisumbing]], a retired [[Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the Philippines]], and their 2 daughters.
